tr: without any others being included or involved
example: a school devoted entirely to the needs of problem children
he works for Mr. Smith exclusively
the burden of proof rests on the prosecution alone
a privilege granted only to him

value.def: Exclusively is used to refer to situations or activities that involve only the thing or things mentioned, and nothing else.

example.ex: Instruction in these subjects in undergraduate classes is almost exclusively by lecture.
example.tran: 本科生的这几门课程几乎完全是通过讲座教授的。

gramarinfo.label: ADV with cl/group, ADV with v

value.tran: 排他地;独占地;专有地;完全地
